Introduction
Across all sports, the home team tends to win at a higher clip when
adjusting for team quality. To properly calibrate our ratings, this must
be factored in. We are going to look at a few different ways to
calculate the effect playing at home creates.
Ways To Analyze Home Court
Advantage
We are going to look at three different ways to calculate home court
advantage. We will discuss the pros and cons of each method to help
determine how much playing at home helps.
All Home Games
The simplest method is to just calculate the winning percentage of
games not played at a neutral site. When we plot that we see the home
court win percentage is around 64-66% for all but the most recent two
years.


